# Copy to sanitize-strings.conf and add one replacement per line (conf is gitignored).
#
# Format:  oldstring:newstring
# Split on the FIRST colon only — newstring may contain colons.
#
# Put longer / more specific strings first so partial replacements do not
# leave fragments of internal names behind.
#
# Do NOT put real internal hostnames on active (non-comment) lines in this
# example file — pre-commit would rewrite them. Keep live pairs only in
# sanitize-strings.conf (gitignored).
#
# Suggested categories for a local sanitize-strings.conf:
#   <full-vcenter-fqdn>:vcsa.vmware.lab.example.com
#   <lab-dns-suffix>:lab.example.com
#   <aap-route-fqdn>:aap.example.com
#   <ocp-apps-suffix>:.apps.cluster.example.com
#   <cluster-dns-suffix>:cluster.example.com
#   <lab-shortname>:demolab
#   <local-username>:operator

your-hostname.example.com:lennysh-laptop
